@SG_ML_HEADER_detaileddescription Detailed Description
@SG_ML_L007007SGLHashsglhash provides a hash function struct for use with SGEXTN Containers, this should be used most of the time when using @SG_ML_L00F00FSGLUnorderedSetsglunorderedset, @SG_ML_L014014SGLUnorderedMultiSetsglunorderedmultiset, or @SG_ML_L00F00FSGLUnorderedMapsglunorderedmap. You need hash() defined to use @SG_ML_L00B00BSGLEqualsTosglequalsto with custom structs. @SG_ML_L007007SGLHashsglhash works with all object pointers and C++ builtin types although they do not define hash(). This is a template based class with no separate source file.
@SG_ML_BLANKLINE
@SG_ML_HEADER_implementationdetails Implementation Details
@SG_ML_L007007SGLHashsglhash calls hash() on the corresponding data type if it is a custom struct. If it is a C++ builtin type or a object pointer, @SG_ML_L007007SGLHashsglhash is implemented separately but still works. Implementations of hash() use @SG_ML_L010010SGLHashAlgorithmsglhashalgorithm.
@SG_ML_BLANKLINE
